    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're just telling me to keep suffering in the name of \"strength.\" what if there isn't a \"worth it\" part left? if someone looks at the math and decides the cost of living is just higher than anything they could ever get back, isn't it just an honest, rational choice to call it quits? isn't there some kind of dignity in just stopping?",
